<blockquote>
<p>Maybe the update function isn’t being called?</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>The update function is called internally by our odometry thread, by default at 100 Hz on <span class="abbreviation">CAN<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Controller Area Network"></template></span> 2.0 and 250 Hz on <span class="abbreviation">CAN<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Controller Area Network"></template></span> FD.</p>
<aside class="quote no-group" data-username="Joseph_Amador" data-post="6" data-topic="482024" data-full="true">
<div class="title">
<div class="quote-controls"></div>
<img loading="lazy" alt="" width="24" height="24" src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/919ad9/48.png" class="avatar"> Joseph_Amador:</div>
<blockquote>
<p>The code I shared doesn’t have that but I have tried that and it didn’t seem to change anything.</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>Can you look at the output of <code>Utils.fpgaToCurrentTime(LLposeEstimate.timestampSeconds)</code> compared to <code>Utils.getCurrentTimeSeconds()</code>? They should be fairly close (within 0.050 seconds), given that all the function does is take the difference between our clock and the FPGA clock and add it to the FPGA timestamp.</p>","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"posts_count":14,"updated_at":"2025-01-16T04:19:38.331Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":7,"quote_count":2,"incoming_link_count":15,"reads":179,"readers_count":178,"score":115.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":482024,"topic_slug":"ctre-swerve-addvisionmeasurment-having-no-effect","display_username":"Benjamin Hall","primary_group_name":"CTRE","flair_name":"CTRE","flair_url":"/uploads/default/original/3X/1/b/1bd2b430e1bb6427d1c6504ff6abcd31de851a6d.png","flair_bg_color":"","flair_color":"","flair_group_id":57,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":48146,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Software Engineering Intern at CTR Electronics"},"post_url":"/t/ctre-swerve-addvisionmeasurment-having-no-effect/482024/8","custom_user_title":"Software Engineering Intern at CTR Electronics","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3484252,"name":"Joseph Gonzalo Amador","username":"Joseph_Amador","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/919ad9/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-01-16T04:30:41.010Z","cooked":"<p>I can check that tomorrow.</p>
<p>In the meantime, I captured this log file from earlier today. The Manual pose is my limelight’s pose estimate and Fused PoseDBL is the pose I got from getstate().pose.<br>
<a class="attachment" href="/uploads/short-url/k5n4osfsrB1UR8DmqTbCsA9xHKV.zip">FRC_20250115_170742.zip</a> (3.1 MB)</p>
<p>Running this code:<br>
<a href="https://github.com/TheMathWiz56/2848_Reefscape/tree/31d81315a0be0cd36f0ce6c3a5760071783bc21e" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">https://github.com/TheMathWiz56/2848_Reefscape/tree/31d81315a0be0cd36f0ce6c3a5760071783bc21e</a></p>","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"posts_count":14,"updated_at":"2025-01-16T04:30:41.010Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":8,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":4,"reads":178,"readers_count":177,"score":60.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":482024,"topic_slug":"ctre-swerve-addvisionmeasurment-having-no-effect","display_username":"Joseph Gonzalo Amador","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/TheMathWiz56/2848_Reefscape/tree/31d81315a0be0cd36f0ce6c3a5760071783bc21e","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"GitHub - TheMathWiz56/2848_Reefscape at 31d81315a0be0cd36f0ce6c3a5760071783bc21e","clicks":23},{"url":"/uploads/short-url/k5n4osfsrB1UR8DmqTbCsA9xHKV.zip","internal":true,"reflection":false,"clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":48146,"username":"bhall-ctre","name":"Benjamin Hall","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/bhall-ctre/{size}/198180_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":57242,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Joseph Amador"},"post_url":"/t/ctre-swerve-addvisionmeasurment-having-no-effect/482024/9","custom_user_title":"Joseph Amador","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3484263,"name":"Benjamin Hall","username":"bhall-ctre","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/bhall-ctre/{size}/198180_2.png","created_at":"2025-01-16T04:49:53.838Z","cooked":"<p>In that code base, I see a commit where you called <code>addVisionMeasurement</code> without using <code>Utils.fpgaToCurrentTime</code>, and then a commit using a local pose estimator with <code>Utils.fpgaToCurrentTime</code>. However, those would be backwards; our <code>addVisionMeasurement</code> requires <code>Utils.fpgaToCurrentTime</code>, while your local one (which is WPILib’s) requires that you do NOT use <code>Utils.fpgaToCurrentTime</code>.</p>
<p>The log also looks like it was without any usage of <code>Utils.fpgaToCurrentTime</code>, although it’s hard to tell because timestamps aren’t logged.</p>
<p>Based on that, it’s not clear to me if you’ve tried using our <code>addVisionMeasurement</code> with the <code>Utils.fpgaToCurrentTime</code> change. If you haven’t, then I would revert the switch to a local pose estimator, add the call to <code>Utils.fpgaToCurrentTime</code>, and check the results.</p>","post_number":10,"post_type":1,"posts_count":14,"updated_at":"2025-01-16T04:52:21.330Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":9,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":14,"reads":161,"readers_count":160,"score":142.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":482024,"topic_slug":"ctre-swerve-addvisionmeasurment-having-no-effect","display_username":"Benjamin Hall","primary_group_name":"CTRE","flair_name":"CTRE","flair_url":"/uploads/default/original/3X/1/b/1bd2b430e1bb6427d1c6504ff6abcd31de851a6d.png","flair_bg_color":"","flair_color":"","flair_group_id":57,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":57242,"username":"Joseph_Amador","name":"Joseph Gonzalo Amador","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/919ad9/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":48146,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Software Engineering Intern at CTR Electronics"},"post_url":"/t/ctre-swerve-addvisionmeasurment-having-no-effect/482024/10","custom_user_title":"Software Engineering Intern at CTR Electronics","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":2}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":true,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3484266,"name":"Joseph Gonzalo Amador","username":"Joseph_Amador","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/919ad9/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-01-16T04:54:19.943Z","cooked":"<p>Gotchya, tomorrow I will switch back to <span class="abbreviation">CTRE<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Cross The Road Electronics"></template></span>’s poseEstimator and try changing FPGA to current time.</p>","post_number":11,"post_type":1,"posts_count":14,"updated_at":"2025-01-16T04:54:19.943Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":10,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":155,"readers_count":154,"score":46.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":482024,"topic_slug":"ctre-swerve-addvisionmeasurment-having-no-effect","display_username":"Joseph Gonzalo Amador","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":48146,"username":"bhall-ctre","name":"Benjamin Hall","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/bhall-ctre/{size}/198180_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":57242,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Joseph Amador"},"post_url":"/t/ctre-swerve-addvisionmeasurment-having-no-effect/482024/11","custom_user_title":"Joseph Amador","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3484267,"name":"Jonah Bonner","username":"jonahb55","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/jonahb55/{size}/194474_2.png","created_at":"2025-01-16T04:54:47.175Z","cooked":"<p>It looks like you’re getting the pose estimate from the <code>get_manual_LL_Estimate()</code> method, which does not read a timestamp. I would recommend using the <code>getBotPoseEstimate()</code> method from <code>LimelightHelpers</code> as a starting point, which reads the timestamp from NetworkTables with appropriate latency adjustments.</p>
<p>Of course, you also need to properly convert to <span class="abbreviation">CTRE<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Cross The Road Electronics"></template></span>’s non-FPGA time base as explained previously.</p>","post_number":12,"post_type":1,"posts_count":14,"updated_at":"2025-01-16T04:54:47.175Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":5,"reads":153,"readers_count":152,"score":75.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":482024,"topic_slug":"ctre-swerve-addvisionmeasurment-having-no-effect","display_username":"Jonah Bonner","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":44471,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"6328M/WPILib"},"post_url":"/t/ctre-swerve-addvisionmeasurment-having-no-effect/482024/12","custom_user_title":"6328M/WPILib","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3484268,"name":"Joseph Gonzalo Amador","username":"Joseph_Amador","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/919ad9/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-01-16T04:56:23.367Z","cooked":"<p>Will do. I switched to the manual <span class="abbreviation">LL<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Limelight, an integrated vision coprocessor"></template></span> estimate since the wpibotpose_orb_wpiblue isn’t working properly with the new field size.</p>","post_number":13,"p